description: JD Bancshares, Inc. provides various banking products and services to individuals and businesses primarily in Southwest Louisiana. The company offers checking, demand, savings, individual retirement, and certificates of deposit accounts; commercial, business, real estate, agricultural, lot, mobile home, consumer, and mortgage loans; credit cards; and overdraft protection, wire transfer, bill payment, safe deposit box, automatic clearance house origination, online and mobile banking, merchant, and other banking services. It also provides investment products and services, including fixed and variable annuities, mutual funds, life and disability insurance, stocks and bonds, tax-advantaged investments, long-term care insurance, retirement plans, money market funds, unit investment trusts, brokered certificates of deposit, and U.S. government obligations. In addition, the company offers estate and trust services, such as estate and tax planning, investment management, trust administration of revocable and irrevocable trusts, curatorship/tutorship administration, special needs trusts, charitable trusts, successions, 401(k) rollovers, and retirement plans. It operates 21 full service branch offices. JD Bancshares, Inc. was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Jennings, Louisiana.
